        "client_msg_id": "c16542d7-6b4d-4aa8-8883-54955b50580c",
        "text": "I used WordStar a bit on a CP\/M machine in the 80s. It was very well designed given the limitations of those machines.\n\nOne thing I’d like point out in Sawyer’s discussion is that WordStar has one of the best attributes any piece of software can have: it rewards mastery. One can argue that the keyboard shortcuts are harder to discover than, say, drop down menus actuated with a mouse, but once they’re in your hands you can move faster than in any mouse-y interface.",
